The President has issued a statement on the Cybersecurity Framework, emphasizing the importance of defending the nation against cyber threats. The National Institute of Standards and Technology has worked with the private sector to develop this framework, which highlights best practices and standards for managing cyber risk. The President believes that the framework is a turning point, but acknowledges that more work needs to be done to enhance cybersecurity. He emphasizes the importance of securing cyberspace and maintaining an open, secure, and reliable internet. The President urges Congress to pass cybersecurity legislation that protects both the nation and individual privacy and civil liberties. In the meantime, his Administration will continue to take action to protect the nation from cyber threats.